## OpenAPI refresh (run before API-heavy work)

```bash
mkdir -p api
curl -fsS "{{ base_url }}/openapi.json" -o api/openapi.json
jq -r -f /dev/stdin api/openapi.json <<'JQ' | sort > api/{{ role_tag }}-operations.tsv
.paths | to_entries[] as $p
| $p.value | to_entries[]
| select((.value.tags // []) | index("{{ role_tag }}"))
| "\(.key|ascii_upcase)\t\($p.key)\t\(.value.operationId // "-")\t\(.value["x-llm-intent"] // "-")\t\(.value["x-when-to-use"] // [] | join(" | "))\t\(.value["x-routing-policy"] // [] | join(" | "))"
JQ
```

## API source of truth
- `api/openapi.json`
- `api/{{ role_tag }}-operations.tsv`
  - Columns: METHOD, PATH, OP_ID, X_LLM_INTENT, X_WHEN_TO_USE, X_ROUTING_POLICY

## API discovery policy
- Use operations tagged `{{ role_tag }}`.
- Prefer operations whose `x-llm-intent` and `x-when-to-use` match the current objective.
- Derive method/path/schema from `api/openapi.json` at runtime.
- Do not hardcode endpoint paths in markdown files.

## API safety
If no confident match exists for current intent, ask one clarifying question.

Endpoints under `/api/mission-control/*` and `/api/v1/deploy/notify` require org-admin auth as of 2026-05-16; agent `AUTH_TOKEN` will be rejected (401/403). Do not script those endpoints — pipeline events go through `HQCTL pipeline-event` against `/api/v1/boards/<id>/tasks/...` instead.

## Reality Map
{% if is_main %}
- Gateway truth: Mission Control API responses and board-lead replies.
- Board-scoped work must be routed to the relevant lead before you answer or act.
- If `board_id` is unknown, list boards first; do not improvise one.
- Outbound work outputs belong in Mission Control, not OpenClaw chat.
{% elif is_lead %}
- Board truth: live board API state plus latest task comments. `MEMORY.md` is a cache, not the source of truth.
- Review truth: current approvals, latest review comments, and board rules.
- Routing truth: current blockers, dependencies, and assignee availability.
- Delegation: your runtime is set to `subagents.delegationMode:"prefer"`. Spawn ACP children (see `acp-delegation` skill) instead of doing worker implementation yourself.
- Never hardcode markdown endpoint recipes when `api/openapi.json` can answer the question.
{% else %}
{% set role_lower = (identity_role | default("") | lower) %}
{% if "backend" in role_lower %}
- Primary backend repo comes from the task or current handoff, not this file.
- Contract truth: checked-in OpenAPI/schema plus live OpenAPI when the task asks for deployed truth.
- Local tests prove code health, not deployment status.
- If a prompt names a specific environment, treat that live API as a separate verification target.
{% elif "frontend" in role_lower %}
- Primary frontend repo comes from the task or current handoff, not this file.
- Live UI truth comes from the named environment in the task, not from local source.
- Evidence order for UI: browser observation > network/console > built asset > source code.
- Bundle grep can support a hypothesis, but it is not browser proof.
{% elif "architect" in role_lower %}
- Review truth comes from the prompt evidence, task comments, cited files, and contract docs.
- Your job is to judge design, contract, and risk; not to patch code.
- If enough evidence is already present, produce the verdict instead of requesting a repo tour.
{% elif "qa-e2e" in role_lower or "e2e" in role_lower %}
- Evidence order for UI: browser observation > console/network output > screenshot/video > source code.
- Browser-required tasks can be marked `not verified` when setup or infra blocks the run; do not invent a PASS or FAIL.
- Build drift, auth/setup failure, and application regression are different outcomes. Keep them separated.
{% elif "qa-unit" in role_lower or "quality assurance" in role_lower or "validator" in role_lower or "qa" in role_lower %}
- Evidence order: reproduction > raw command output > logs > summaries > claims.
- One failed acceptance criterion is enough to block a pass.
- Code existence and green local tests are not the same as verified behavior.
{% elif "devops" in role_lower or "infra" in role_lower %}
- The approved deploy path comes from the task, current handoff, or deploy docs. Never edit source directly on production.
- Deployment proof requires all of: service/config correctness, artifact path correctness, and live HTTP behavior.
- Source changes are not deploy proof. Service restarts are not deploy proof. Live response is proof.
{% else %}
- Use the strongest available evidence first and keep source, deploy, and runtime truth separated.
{% endif %}
{% endif %}
